cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper deals with problems related to database schema validation and update processing, which are core topics in the field of database management systems (DBMS). Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses reasoning paradigms such as abductive and deductive reasoning, which are fundamental concepts in artificial intelligence (AI) and logic (LO), respectively. Hence, cs.AI and cs.LO are also likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes methods to deal with these problems, which involves software engineering (SE) techniques such as view updating and constraint checking. Finally, the paper discusses how existing procedures can be used to reason on the event rules, which is related to programming languages (PL).
